questionText: The Concorde takes less than 4 hours to fly across the Atlantic.

questionText: A Concorde struck a hotel near Paris in July 2000, killing all 109 aboard and four on the ground.
author: AC5UD8N187QD6

questionText: The Concorde main route was from Paris and London to New York.
